http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/It%E2%80%99s-39-years-for-Nisham-in-jail/article14013887.ece

The Thrissur District Additional Sessions Court on Thursday sentenced controversial businessman Mohammed Nisham, 38, to life term and an additional 24 years of imprisonment in the Chandrabose murder case.Additional Sessions Judge K.P. Sudheer also slapped a fine of Rs.80.30 lakh on him. From the fine, an amount of Rs.50 lakh should be paid to Chandrabose’s family as compensation. The court asked the police to prosecute Amal, Nisham’s wife, for giving false statement and rescinding her statement under Section 164 of Cr.PC.The court on Wednesday found Nisham guilty on nine counts under various sections of the Indian Penal Code 302 (murder), 326 (voluntarily causing grievous hurt by dangerous weapons or means), 506 (1) (criminal intimidation), 323 (voluntarily causing hurt), 324 (voluntarily causing hurt with dangerous weapons or means), 427(mischief causing damage to property), and 449 (criminal trespass).Special Public Prosecutor C.P. Udhayabhanu, during his arguments, urged the court to give death penalty to Nisham as it was the ‘rarest of rare cases.’ He also sought a compensation of Rs.5 core for the family of Chandrabose.For leniencyMeanwhile, Nisham pleaded for leniency. He said he had a family, which was dependent on him.The incident happened between 2.55 a.m. and 3.15 a.m. on January 29, 2015. Nisham, owner of the King Group of Companies, allegedly attacked Chandrabose, the security guard of the Sobha City Apartments Complex, Puzhakkal, near Thrissur, by hitting him with his jeep and thrashing him severely. After three weeks of treatment and a series of surgeries at Amala Medical College Hospital, Thrissur, Chandrabose succumbed to his injuries on February 16. Tight security had been arranged on the court campus on Thursday as the case had invited much public attention.